Patch Set 8:

> LGTM, but I don't understand why this change and the others (97281, 97294, 97308, 97310, 97346) have not been integrated together in a same change or even better in the change related to the Phosphorus migration.

Thx for the review.
Here are the 2 reasons:

first one: the original change was owned by Gilles and as previously agreed, I wanted to interfere at minimum on other people's changes.Especially here because Gilles was working on GNPy meanwhile.

second one: I am a KISS adept and I prefer "atomic" simple and small commits as explained in openstack wiki.
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GitCommitMessages#Structural_split_of_changes
They are more easy to review and rebase with others changes if someone else works on another topic.
This also ease the commiters'work.
In my opinion, versions bumps should better be handled as a set of several changes with a same topic rather than a big commit.

Hope this helps
Guillaume
